title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-12-30
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, Row Jimmy, Big River, Peggy-O, Passenger, Ramble On Rose, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Saint Stephen-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues, E: Good Lovin'

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text: Good things come to those who wait Finally get to listen to this awesome Winterland show in it's entirety. The sound quality is perfect! Thank you Charlie. Keep em coming!

Twas the night before New Years And all through the house the GD was rocking all the kids. Another great show I had the joy of attending. So fun to listen almost 40 years later. Oh to be 20 again and living the dream. Thank you to all that have done such a wonderful job preserving this music.
Me and My Uncle This is a great overall show with excellent sound quality from Charlie Miller. 1977 remains my favorite year.
Winter Wonder-land! Great show 40 years ago today! Great SBD source, epic St. Stephen too

My first Dead show! This was the first day of the rest of my life - caught 2 tickets as a Christmas present, and my college roommate flew up from LA to go with me. Wow, what a show! Thoroughly enjoyed the set list, Jerry ripped through  Big River into Peggy O and I was hooked. Became a tape collector the following year, and amassed quite a collection over the next 30 years. This  is still one of my favorite shows. Special shoutout to Mr. Charlie Miller for restoring the SBD to great fidelity. Enjoy!
